Lets go through the classes and see what each class does in a raiding situation:
Bard
-----
Raiding Role: As His Description States, The Bard Is A Jack Of All Trades In A Raid.  He Hastes His Group, He Does Damage, He Sings Resists, He Sings Mana Regen Songs, Ect.
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Beastlord
----------
Raiding Role: ???
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: ???

Cleric
-------
Raiding Role: Heal The Tanks, Rez Dead People, And Buff Everyone With Aegoism, and the like.
Vital To Raid: Yes
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Druid
------
Raiding Role: Dot the Mobs, Play Secondary Healer, Buff Up Resists, SoW People.
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Enchanter
-----------
Raiding Role: Mez Adds,  C2/C3 Everyone, Speed The Tanks, Die...
Vital To Raid: Yes
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Magician
----------
Raiding Role: CoH, Occasionally Use Their Pet To Deal Damage
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Monk
---------
Raiding Role: Pull Stuff, Do Damage
Vital To Raid: No *Other People With FD Can Pull, I've Seen It Done*
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Necromancer
------------
Raiding Role: Feed Healers/Enchanters Mana, Dot Mobs, Occasionally Use Pet To Deal Damage
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Paladin
---------
Raiding Role: Deal Damage, Heal Themselves, Rarely They Also Tank
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Ranger
---------
Raiding Role: Deal Damage
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Shadow Knight
--------------
Raiding Role: Deal Damage, Dot Mobs, If No Monks Use FD To Pull, Tank Mobs
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Shaman
----------
Raiding Role: Debuff Mobs, Buff Teammates, Dot/Slow Mobs
Vital To  Raid: Most Of The Time No, But Some Of The Time Yes
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes

Warrior
---------
Raiding Role: Tank Mobs
Vital To Raid: Yes, Though A Paladin/Shadow Knight Can Sometimes Be Substituted Depending On The Situation
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes, Even Though They Are Mana Sponges

Wizard
--------
Raiding Role: Nuke Mobs
Vital To Raid: No
Good To Have On A Raid: Yes


========================================================
As You Can See, There Are Very Few Classes That Are Vital To  Raids, But All Classes Contribute To Raids And Make Things Go Smoother, The Bottom Line Is, Play What You Enjoy Playing, You Will Still Get To Raid.

